ClariFit IR Column Grouping

Plug-in Type: Dynamic Action
Summary: Displays IR Column Groups on top of the column headers.

Depends:
 $.console.js  - http://code.google.com/p/js-console-wrapper

Configure IR Column Groups

- Edit IR
- Go to Column Groups region
- Click the Add Group button
- Enter group information and click the Create button
- Repeat if necessary to create more groups

- In the Column Attributes region you can assign a group to each column.

How to implement the IR Column Group Plugin

- On the page with the IR create a Dynamic Action
- Select Advanced
- Name: IR Column Group  (this can be whatever you want)
- Event: After Refresh  (under Framework Events)
  Selection Type: DOM Object (do not select region - see below)
  DOM Object: apexir_REPORT  (case sensitive)
  Condition: No Condition
  Click the Next button
- Action: ClariFit IR Column Grouping
- Selection Type: (leave blank)
 

The reason why it's recommended that you set the Selection Type to DOM object and not region, is that by default Interactive Reports region template is "No Template". This means that there's no way to identify the IR using this method. Using the DOM object guarantees that the Dynamic Action will work regardless of region template.

How to configure for ALL Interactive Reports

This plugin can be easily setup for all interactive reports. Just replicate the previous steps but create the Dynamic Action on Page 0.
